  "text": "Very few studies have tested stepping up (or stepping down) treatment, although one exception is the WISDOM study that was designed to test withdrawal of inhaled corticosteroids (ICS). [CITATION_1] Another issue is that most trials are parallel-group comparisons in which the treatment is determined by the randomization process rather than by the treating physician.",
